ASSEMBLY CONCURRENT RESOLUTION—Authorizing
additional reimbursement for travel in certain
circumstances.
1 RESOLVED BY THE ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, THE
2 SENATE CONCURRING, That to offset the increased cost of flights, a
3 legislator may apply for reimbursement for travel of 50 miles or
4 more between the legislator’s home and Carson City, Nevada, to
5 serve during the 83rd (2025) Session of the Nevada Legislature by
6 submitting a claim for the reimbursement of any amount the
7 legislator is required to pay for such travel which exceeds the
8 amount authorized to be provided pursuant to NRS 218A.645, up to
9 a maximum amount of $10,000 per legislator; and be it further
10 RESOLVED, That the amount of any such claim that is approved
11 be verified, processed and paid in the same manner as claims
12 pursuant to NRS 218A.645; and be it further
13 RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon
14 adoption.
